sentences: Lage Fosheim Lund (born 12 December 1977) is a Norwegian jazz guitarist.
In 2002, Lund was the recipient of a Fulbright Foundation grant, which gave him the opportunity to move to New York City.
In 2003, he entered the Juilliard School scholarship jazz program and graduated in 2005. He won the Thelonious Monk International Jazz Competition in 2005.
Inspired with Rale Micic, John Abercrombie, Peter Bernstein (ArtistShare, 2016)
Seamus Blake, Way Out Willy (Criss Cross, 2007)
Orlando le Fleming, From Brooklyn with Love (Nineteen-Eight, 2010)
Jimmy Greene, While Looking Up (Mack Avenue, 2020)
